  "doc_id": "197",
  "text": "The original Delphi study was run in the 1950s and 1960s by the RAND corporation to help the US Government determine the nuclear capabilities of the Soviet Union [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . They were studying the unknown military futures market by asking a variety of experts to answer a battery of questions. The answers were collated and then distributed back to the experts for additional rounds of answering the same questions -but critically, with the collective opinions of the other experts to aid their synthesis.",
